for the automatic compilation of documents. To know if any source files
have changed since the last compilation, LaTeXMk keeps a text database of
all dependencies by the inspection of LOG files. For example, if I run the
command latexmk -pdf source2e.tex, the attached file sample2e.fdb_latexmk
will be created and will contain a complete list of dependencies together
with last modified timestamps, file sizes, and hashes. Given a backing
store that can fetch these files, this text database seems almost
sufficient as a recipe for reproducibly recompiling the TeX document.

